description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infection Prevention and Control Lead Nurse – Band 8A/B (depending on experience) – Infection Control – 37.5 hours per week – Permanent &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Could you help West Suffolk Hospital to deliver the best quality and safest care to our local community?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here in Bury St Edmunds we enjoy a lovely place to live and a friendly and caring place to work. Every day we value great team work, improving and adapting, communicating well and taking pride in what we do for patients. The West Suffolk NHS Foundation Trust is passionate about reducing rates of infection and improving the quality of our patient’s care across the whole health economy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you too are passionate about leading and influencing infection prevention and control, then we would like you to join our Trust and be at the forefront of delivering best practice in many diverse areas. A full-time Band 8A/B (depending on your experience) opportunity has arisen for an experienced infection prevention and control nurse to lead the team at the West Suffolk NHS Foundation Trust, and our integrated community services. The team includes an infection control doctor, a band 8A/B lead nurse and two band 6 nurses. We work closely with our local STP/Clinical Commissioning Group infection prevention lead as well as leads in neighbouring Trusts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fantastic opportunity to join the Trust at the beginning of a significant period of planned development and transformation of services. We are looking for an passionate, well organised and confident leader who can communicate effectively and work with staff from all backgrounds and levels to fulfil the full potential of the service to support this reconfiguration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is available to clinicians with a minimum of education to masters (or equivalent level) or willing to undertake, evidence of infection prevention control qualification / education, excellent communications skills, expert role model, committed to delivering high quality services, motivated and passionate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details or to arrange an informal visit contact interim Chief Nurse and DIPC Sue Wilkinson on 01284 713500 or email susan.wilkinson@wsh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have the necessary skills, experience and qualities to help us to put patients first, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**In order to improve efficiency, all correspondence relating to this vacancy, &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;including invitations to interview will be by email only&lt;/span&gt;, via NHS Jobs. Would you therefore please ensure you check your emails on a regular basis**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In submitting an application form, you authorise West Suffolk NHS FT to confirm any previous NHS service details via the Inter Authority Transfer (IAT) process, should you be appointed to the post. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CAR PARKING&lt;/strong&gt; - This post &lt;strong&gt;does&lt;/strong&gt; entitle you to apply to park on the Hospital site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate for this post will be required to apply for a Disclosure &amp; Barring Service (DBS) Disclosure at Enhanced level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For Band 1 and Band 2 posts, the cost of the DBS Disclosure will be met by the Trust. However, any employees at Band 1 and Band 2 who leave the Trust within six months of commencing their post will have a £10 administration fee deducted from their final salary. For posts at Band 3 and above, the cost of the Disclosure will be met by the appointed employee and deducted in instalments from their salary over a period of three months. If the employee leaves the Trust within three months of commencing their post, any outstanding payments will be deducted from their final pay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All applicants should click on the link entitled “How will my application be processed?” prior to submitting their application form.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The closing date for this vacancy may change if we receive a strong response. Please ensure that you apply for any post you are interested in as soon as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
